  "notes": [
    {
      "title": "Sound Plurals (جمع السالم)",
      "titleArabic": "الْجَمْعُ السَّالِم",
      "content": [
        "Sound plurals are regular plurals formed by adding endings to the singular. Masculine sound plural adds ونَ (nominative) or ينَ (genitive/accusative). Feminine sound plural adds اتٌ.",
        "Sound masculine plurals are typically used for male rational beings (humans). Sound feminine plurals are used for female rational beings and some inanimate nouns."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Masculine sound plural: مُدَرِّسٌ → مُدَرِّسُونَ (teachers, m.)",
        "Feminine sound plural: طَالِبَةٌ → طَالِبَاتٌ (students, f.)",
        "The ة is dropped when adding اتٌ",
        "Genitive masculine plural: مُدَرِّسِينَ"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مُدَرِّسُونَ", "english": "teachers (m.)" },
        { "arabic": "طَالِبَاتٌ", "english": "students (f.)" },
        { "arabic": "مُسْلِمُونَ", "english": "Muslims (m.)" },
        { "arabic": "مُسْلِمَاتٌ", "english": "Muslims (f.)" }
      ]
    }
  ],
